SIMPLE: topical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Topical
<hw>Top"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>topique</ets>, LL. <ets>topicus</ets>, Gr. <?/. See <er>Topic</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a place;
limited; logical application; <as>as, a <ex>topical</ex> remedy; a
<ex>topical</ex> claim or privilege</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Rhet. & logic)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or
consisting of, a topic or topics; according to topics.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Resembling a topic, or general maxim; hence, not
demonstrative, but merely probable, as an argument.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Evidences of fact can be no more than <qex>topical</qex> and
probable.</q> <rj><au>Sir M. Hale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Topically</ent>⟦br⟧
